{
  "texts": [
    "And this once again by simply choosing among the diverse explanations, without any need to impose constraints on the counterfactual generating search.",
    "This shows the arbitrariness/disagreement of the methods and the power that it brings to the user of counterfactual generating methods.",
    "A user can include, as well as avoid, almost any desired feature in the given explanation.",
    "This example clearly illustrates the possible existence of the disagreement problem and the ethical consequences resulting from this existence.",
    "In the following sections, we examine how easy it is to abuse the disagreement problem by malicious agents and the driving factors that cause the disagreement problem."
  ]
}